* float *p[4]
An array of pointers of type float of size 4. It's equivalent to:
[f32* f32* f32* f32*]

* float (*p)[4]
A single pointer to an array of floats of size 4. It's equivalent to a pointer that can point to:
[1.0f 1.0f 2.0f 2.0f ...]

-----
Additionally:
* const f32 (*const_matrix)[MAX_N];
A single pointer to an array of size MAX_N of constant floats.

* f32 (*matrix)[MAX_N];
A single pointer to an array of size MAX_N of floats.
